"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The replace() method is called without the inplace parameter set to True, which means it returns a new DataFrame with the replacements made, but does not modify the original DataFrame. To apply the changes to df['l2'], the result of the replace() method should be assigned back to df['l2'] or the inplace parameter should be set to True.\",\n  \"patch\": \"8c8\\n< df['l2'].replace(to_replace=r'^\\u001d+$', value=0, regex=True)\\n---\\n> df['l2'] = df['l2'].replace(to_replace=r'^\\u001d+$', value=0, regex=True)\\n\"\n}"